snippet: A week and a half after Typhoon Haiyan struck, more health workers are tending to the injured and some supplies are getting through to the interior.
abstract: Medical care is finally beginning to improve in areas hit by Typhoon Haiyan, with 62 foreign or Filipino medical teams working in areas with the most damage.
lead_paragraph: A week and a half after Typhoon Haiyan struck, more health workers are tending to the injured and some supplies are getting through to the interior.

headline.main: Medical Care Improves in Storm-Hit Areas, Though Many Are Still Out of Reach
headline.print_headline: Medical Care Improves in Storm-Hit Areas, Though Many Are Still Out of Reach
